Add fresh-test reset script (wipe runtime data, keep settings)

- scripts/reset-test-data.sh: empties the running container's workspace
  volume for a clean test while preserving settings — API keys (the separate
  bookclaw-vault volume is untouched) and app config (config/*.json, baked into
  the image). Resolves the workspace + vault volumes from the container's mounts
  (no name-guessing); stop -> empty volume via a throwaway container on the same
  image (--entrypoint find -delete: no pull, bypasses the entrypoint wrapper) ->
  start -> wait for healthy. Same container is reused, so the bearer token and
  vault key persist.
- Safety: prints a KEEP/WIPE plan and requires typing RESET (-y/--yes skips it
  for scripted use). Best-effort post-reset project count.
- Verified on Mercury: projects 171 -> 0, soul/identity wiped, vault.enc +
  user.json preserved, openrouter still an active (key-backed) provider.
